data-triple-N3.o: "An arcade game (or coin-op) is a coin-operated entertainment machine, usually installed in public businesses, such as restaurants, bars, and particularly amusement arcades. Most arcade games are video games, pinball machines, electro-mechanical games, redemption games, and merchandisers. The golden age of arcade video games lasted from the late 1970s to the mid-1990s."@en
